content: AWESOME RECIPE! Made this last night. If you like chicken thighs, you will love this! Ingredients: 2 lbs. chicken thighs - skin on, 1/3 cup soy sauce.. ponzu sauce.. or tamari, 2 cloves minced garlic, 1 inch knob of minced ginger, 1/3 cup dark brown sugar, cooking oil. Mix all ingredients but the chicken and oil (I just toss everything in the blender). Pour into a gallon size zip top bag. Poke thighs with a fork to allow marinade to better absorb. Add chicken to marinade, seal and set aside 30 to 60 minutes. Remove thighs from marinade and set marinade aside. Heat a splash of oil in a heavy, oven safe pan and sear the thighs.. skin side down.. for 5 minutes without moving them.  Flip them and sear 3 minutes more. Flip them again and add marinade to the pan. Put pan in preheated 400Â° oven for 20 minutes. Enjoy! #abc7NY

content: A whole new way to cook. Sous vide! (pronounced soo veed). My awesome partner Lori got me the white cylander you see here for my b'day. It is a JOULE SOUS VIDE cooker. Basically, the way it works, you put meat or vegetables in a baggie, seal it, put it in water in a pot off the stove, immerse the sous vide machine, set it to the proper temperature, it cooks and you don't have to worry about anything over overcooking. After the protein comes to temperature, you take it out and see it on each side for about a minute. I promise you, the best steak, chicken, fish or vegetables you've ever had. #abc7NY
